Icon Component Sizing

When using icon components from `@/shared/components/Icons.tsx`, do **not** add `w-` or `h-` Tailwind classes (e.g., `className="h-4 w-4"`) unless explicitly asked to do so.

Icon sizing should be controlled via the `size` prop:

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — use the size prop
<CheckIcon size="sm" />
<CheckIcon size="lg" />

// ❌ Incorrect — don't use w-/h- classes for sizing
<CheckIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
```

Available sizes:
- `sm` (default, 20px)
- `lg` (40px)
- `2xl` (64px)

The `className` prop can still be used for other styling purposes (e.g., colors, animations) but not for width/height sizing.
